# Context Routing Map ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: always at session start.
Skip when: never.

Purpose: which docs to load beyond the startup set, and when.

## Default
Start with only `AI_AGENT.md`, `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`, and `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`. Pull deeper docs only on the triggers below.

## Doc Triggers

| Doc | Load when |
|---|---|
| `docs/GAME_PLAN.md` | milestone, scope, sequencing, or next action is unclear |
| `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md` | project purpose, tier, owner intent, or scope boundary is unclear |
| `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md` | choosing AI workflow mode, planning template retrofit, planning cloud-to-local migration, or authorizing overnight local-agent work |
| `docs/CLOSING_CHECKLIST.md` | final handoff, operator asks if everything is done, or operator says run closing checklist |
| `docs/ORCHESTRATION_MAP.md` | assigning work between cloud orchestrator and local worker |
| `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` | commands, tests, worker loop, packet class, or validation rules matter |
| `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md` | issuing a local-worker task |
| `docs/WORKER_RESULT_PACKET.md` | reviewing or returning local-worker output |
| `docs/APPLY_CHECKLIST.md` | worker preparing to return DONE |
| `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` | cloud orchestrator reviewing a DONE result packet |
| `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` | repeated BLOCKED, test-honesty failure, production regression, or architecture unknown |
| `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` | entrypoint, Path ID, workflow, side-effect, or smoke evidence changes |
| `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md` | adding or referencing smoke tests |
| `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md` | adding or changing workflow verification |
| `docs/FEATURE_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md` | designing a non-trivial feature before packet decomposition |
| `docs/STATE_LEDGER_PROTOCOL.md` | packet state, review evidence, budget, or investigator counts need checking/updating |
| `docs/TECH_STACK.md` | architecture, dependency, runtime, or integration boundary decisions |
| `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` | deploy, rollback, secrets, auth, logging, data handling, or release path changes |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | documenting a behavior or operating-model change |
| `AI_CONTEXT.md` | nearby reads are insufficient and a generated map exists |

## Event Triggers

| Event | Load / Run |
|---|---|
| User gives a new directive | Update `docs/GAME_PLAN.md` or `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md` first |
| Before choosing Level 1/2/3 AI workflow mode | `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md` |
| Starting template retrofit on an existing project | `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md` and `docs/TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH.md` |
| Migrating Firebase/cloud app to local server | `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/FEATURE_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md`, `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md`, and `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` |
| Planning overnight local-agent run | `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md`, and `docs/STATE_LEDGER_PROTOCOL.md` |
| Issuing a worker packet | `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md` and `docs/STATE_LEDGER_PROTOCOL.md` |
| Worker returned DONE | `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` mandatory review |
| Worker returned PARTIAL or BLOCKED | `docs/WORKER_RESULT_PACKET.md`, then corrected packet or investigator path |
| Worker returned BLOCKED twice on same Path ID | `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` |
| Active packet times out or returns malformed artifact | `docs/STATE_LEDGER_PROTOCOL.md`; mark `ABANDONED` or `CANCELLED` |
| Test file modified | `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` test-honesty spot-check |
| BUGFIX packet in flight | `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` regression accretion rule |
| New entrypoint or workflow added | `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` and `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md` |
| New smoke test added | `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md` |
| Returning to an existing project for audit, beta readiness, or importing more orchestrator pieces | `docs/TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH.md` §7.5 and `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` |
| Before beta or user acceptance testing | `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md`, `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md`, and manual smoke runbook |
| Runtime smoke is optional or skipped | `scripts/test_smoke.sh` and `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md` |
| Security docs promise a scan | compare `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md`, `.github/workflows/ci.yml`, and `[VERIFY_COMMAND]` |
| About to run unattended overnight | `AI_AGENT.md` unattended and halt rules |
| Behavior change without docs/tests | Stop and add tests/docs or return BLOCKED |
| About to release or merge | Run `[VERIFY_COMMAND]` and project CI/predeploy gate |
| Before final handoff OR operator says "run the closing checklist" | `docs/CLOSING_CHECKLIST.md` |

If an event is not listed here and the AI is unsure, surface to user; do not improvise.

## Skip Rules
- Skip `CHANGELOG.md` for routine implementation unless documenting the change.
- Skip `OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` for isolated local/test-only work.
- Skip `MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` for Tier A doc-only edits with no runtime pathway.
- Skip `TECH_STACK.md` when the task is local and architecture is already clear.

## Escalation
If more than three deeper docs seem necessary before the first edit, stop and ask whether the task is too broad or under-specified.
